    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan for adding `Bun.INI`:\n\n## Plan Overview\n\n**6 files touched total** — 1 new, 5 modified.\n\n### New file: `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`\nA self-contained INI parser/stringifier modeled exactly on `JSON5Object.zig` (the only existing format with both `parse` and `stringify`). The implementation is a simple hand-rolled line-by-line parser — no external dependencies:\n- **`parse`**: skips blanks/comments (`;`/`#`), handles `[section]` headers and `key = value` pairs, throws a descriptive `SyntaxError` on invalid input\n- **`stringify`**: emits top-level scalars first, then `[section]` blocks for nested objects\n\n### Wiring changes (5 files):\n\n| File | What to add |\n|------|------------|\n| `src/bun.js/api.zig` | `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");` |\n| `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` | (4 spots) constant, `@export`, getter function, import |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` | `macro(INI)` between `Glob` and `JSON5` (alphabetical) |\n| `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` | `INI   BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI   DontDelete|PropertyCallback` in `bunObjectTable` |\n| `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` | `namespace INI { parse(...): Record<string, any>; stringify(...): string; }` with JSDoc |",
